5|$|Missoula's <b>system</b> <b>of</b> <b>government</b> {{has changed}} four times since 1883 when an {{aldermanic}} {{form of government}} was approved with the town charter. The city adopted a commission-council form of government in 1911 {{with the opening of}} new City Hall and a council–manager government in 1954 before returning to an aldermanic form of government in 1959. Since January 1, 1997, Missoula has been governed in accordance with the Missoula City Charter, which calls for a mayor-council <b>system</b> <b>of</b> <b>government.</b>|$|E
