50|$|Feudal {{maintenance}} under feudal <b>systems</b> <b>of</b> <b>government,</b> was {{the money}} payment to soldiers {{who fought in}} the interest and at the command of their lord. Such soldiers comprised private armies, each with uniquely identifiable livery. The <b>system</b> <b>of</b> feudal <b>government</b> under which maintenance was paid was most notably present in the late 15th century.|$|R
